6/8/2015 - Marcus - Initial Creation ------------------------------- This script will determine whether or not the specified ConnectWise ticket number actually exists within our production ConnectWise server. This is being created to solve for when technicians accidently enter in an invalid ticket number, which results in creating tickets upon the default board, which undesirable.
Input: @Ticket#@
Output: @IsTicketValid@ (simply the declaration of this variable indicates that the ticket exists).

This script verifies that the LabTech Support user created during Onboarding exists and the credentails are valid. Depending on the results, the account will be created and/or the credentials reset to match what is on file.

Table.ScriptNotes: This script deletes the LabTechSupport user from the partner's LabTech server. This user was created during Onboarding. This script also removes the credentials from the client and location. The Partner may request it to be removed. Any script that rely on creds will FAIL!

This script creates a local Admin user on the Partner's LabTech server as well as creates the same credentials on the client. It then assigns this user to the location the agent belongs to. It also assigns the Default template to the location. ****THE PASSWORD IS RANDOMLY GENERATED AND WILL BE 14 CHARACTERS LONG***

Table.ScriptName: _Check if CD Key is Migration Key
Table.ScriptNotes:
This script takes the provided @CdKey@ variable which is to be defined at a higher scope, and identifies whether or not it is a LabTech migration key.
Should it be a migration key, the variable "@IsMigrationKey@" will be = 1.
